        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Config file sample:\r\n\r\n; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n[production]\r\n; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\ndatabase.adapter                                = pdo_oci\r\ndatabase.params.host                            = my-host\r\n\r\n; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n[staging : production]\r\n; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\ndatabase.params.host                            = ;\r\n\r\nWhen Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Oci checks whether to use a tnsnames.ora entry or use the provided config settings, it uses this structure:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nif (isset($dsn['host'])) {\r\n\/\/ use provided config settings\r\n}else{\r\n\/\/ use tnsnames.ora entry based on dbname\r\n}\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nWhen the config file is provided as above, the variable $dsn['host'] is set to an empty string. I expect this behaviour to look for a tnsnames.ora entry, not to use <empty string> as the hostname.\r\n\r\nPossible fix:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nif (isset($dsn['host']) && $dsn['host']) {\r\n{noformat}"
